Chilean Stocks: Empresas La Polar, Sonda and Vapores Advance

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-10-19T14:11:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/chilean-stocks-empresas-la-polar-sonda-and-vapores-advance.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11 a.m. in Santiago.  The Ipsa index rose 0.7 percent to 4,079.71. The  MSCI Chile (MXCL) 
index rose 1 percent to 2,262.58.  Cia. Sudamericana de Vapores SA (VAPORES CC) rose 0.6
percent to 132 pesos.  Latin America ’s largest container shipping
company announced plans to reduce its workforce by 18 percent.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   gained 4.3 percent to 415
pesos. The department-store operator has called a meeting with
creditors for Nov. 7 to vote on a preventive judicial agreement
to avoid its second bankruptcy in 12 years, according to a paid
advertisement published today in newspaper Diario Financiero.  Sonda SA (SONDA)   increased 2.6 percent to 1,190 pesos,
its third day of gains and its highest price in three weeks.
Chile’s largest information technology company was added to
lender Banco de Credito & Inversiones’ top five list of favorite
Chile stocks. The company is also scheduled to report third-
quarter results Oct. 26.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
